Description:
Middle-down proteomics on mouse tissues demonstrates that H3.3 accumulates to near saturation levels in the chromatin of various somatic mouse tissues by late adulthood. Accumulation of H3.3 is associated with profound changes in genome-wide levels of both individual and
combinatorial H3 modifications.
